<article>
    <h1>Stay in op&#xAD;ti&#xAD;mal health through&#xAD;out COVID-19</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200930/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-30"><time>2020-09-30</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline">By ARUL JOHN</span>
    </section>

    <p>As Sin­ga­pore's cir­cuit breaker re­stric­tions are steadily lifted, there is a danger that we may un­con­sciously in­dulge our­selves in sub-op­ti­mal life­style choices, such as con­sum­ing un­healthy food or ex­er­cis­ing less.</p>
    <p>But a seden­tary life­style is one of the risk fac­tors for car­dio­vas­cu­lar dis­eases, as well as obe­sity, which plagues two in ve adults in the Asia Paci c.</p>
    <p>The lack of proper nu­tri­tion or reg­u­lar phys­i­cal ac­tiv­ity can also lead to low­ered im­mune func­tions while in­creas­ing the risk of de­vel­op­ing chronic ail­ments or non- com­mu­ni­ca­ble dis­eases such as di­a­betes.</p>
    <p>So, it is im­por­tant to have a healthy body and strong im­mune sys­tem, and to take ac­tive steps to emerge stronger and bet­ter for a post-Covid-19 world.</p>
    <p>There are three main in­gre­di­ents - proper nu­tri­tion, an ac­tive life­style and a sup­port­ive com­mu­nity.</p>
    <p>Proper nu­tri­tion</p>
    <p>Adopt a bal­anced diet and in­vest some time to de­velop a deeper un­der­stand­ing of what your body needs and to be able to sep­a­rate the wheat from the cha comes to se­lect­ing from a mul­ti­tude of nu­tri­tion op­tions.</p>
    <p>This en­sures that the prod­ucts we put in our body are bene based on sound nu­tri­tion science and a rig­or­ous qual­ity as­sur­ance pro­gramme.</p>
    <p>We can also take this op­por­tu­nity to pre­pare our own nu­tri­tion-packed meals.</p>
    <p>Ac­tive life­style</p>
    <p>Build an ex­er­cise plan and set re­al­is­tic goals. This will help you to build up your ca­pa­bil­i­ties while low­er­ing the risk of de­vel­op­ing chronic dis­eases, man­ag­ing your weight, re­liev­ing stress and im­prov­ing your mood.</p>
    <p>Sup­port­ive com­mu­nity</p>
    <p>Hav­ing a sup­port­ive com­mu­nity to guide and en­cour­age you can make a huge di ce in up­root­ing un­healthy rou­tines and es­tab­lish­ing health­ier ones.</p>
    <p>Tech­nol­ogy and so­cial me­dia plat­forms can be a boon to help us stay con­nected with one another, keep­ing us com­mit­ted to our diet and ex­er­cise plans.</p>

